      • setBranch

        public void setBranch(Ref branch)
        Sets the branch to the branch, to which the <git-checkout> switched the repository to. This branch should already be existing in the repository. To create a new branch and switch to it, use the -b option while running <git-checkout>.
        Parameters:
        branch -

      • addModifiedFile

        public void addModifiedFile(java.io.File file)
        Adds the modified file to the list of modifiedFiles. When a file is modified locally but has not been committed to the repository and if we try to switch the branch to another branch, the <git-checkout> fails and outputs the list of modified files that are not yet committed unless -f option is used by <git-checkout>.
        Parameters:
        file -

      • addAddedFile

        public void addAddedFile(java.io.File file)
        Adds the newly added file to the list of addedFiles. A newly added file is the one that is added by <git-add> command but had not been committed.
        Parameters:
        file -

      • addDeletedFile

        public void addDeletedFile(java.io.File file)
        Adds the locally deleted file to the list of deletedFiles. A locally deleted file is one that has been removed but has not been removed from repository using <git-rm> command.

        file -
